<module>
  <title><m>-(e)as</m> noun-deriving suffix</title>
  <p></p>
  <p><strong>-(e)as</strong> is a suffix used to create masculine <a href="?xx=nouns/derived_common_nouns">derived common nouns</a> 
    from <a href="?xx=adjectives/adjectives">adjectives</a> or other common nouns.</p>
  <p>De-adjectival examples –</p>
  <ul>
    <li><i>ceart</i> <en>right, just</en> ⇒ <m>ceartas</m> <en>justice</en></li>
  </ul>
  <p>De-nominal examples –</p>
  <ul>
    <li><i>caraid</i> <en>friend</en> ⇒ <m>càirdeas</m> <en>friendship</en></li>
  </ul>
  <p>[cf. <xref id="Gillies1902" p="150"/>]</p>
</module>

